Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 5 of 17: Part 2 Instructions Page 1 of 2: Introduces Part 2 — participants will be asked a number of questions, each requiring a guess of a number. Explains the general payment structure for guesses.).
{{ instruction_screen_5 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 6 of 17: Part 2 Instructions Page 2 of 2: Explains the information structure — participants are told Estimate 1 directly and receive three channel reports, each being the average of Estimate 1 and one other estimate.).
{{ instruction_screen_6 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 7 of 17: Core task explanation: The number equals the average of four estimates. Participant is told Estimate 1 directly and sees three correlated channel reports (each channel = average of Est 1 and one other estimate). Explains the correlation structure.).
{{ instruction_screen_7 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 8 of 17: Alternative/additional core task explanation: Same structure as corr_text — number equals average of four estimates, Estimate 1 given directly, three channel reports each averaging Estimate 1 with one other estimate.).
{{ instruction_screen_8 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 9 of 17: Worked example for Part 2: Shows a concrete numerical example (Est 1=81, Est 2=13, Est 3=100, Est 4=94) illustrating what the channel reports would look like.).
{{ instruction_screen_9 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 10 of 17: Payment selection rule for Part 2: If Part 2 is the part-that-counts, one question is randomly selected and the payment allocated in that question is distributed.).
{{ instruction_screen_10 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 11 of 17: Control treatment payment rule: Explains that a bonus of X cents is allocated to the participant if their guess is correct (guess range contains the right number), and no bonus otherwise.).
{{ instruction_screen_11 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 12 of 17: Overestimate treatment payment rule: Explains that X cents go to self if guess is too high, 150 cents go to charity if guess is too low, and X cents go to self if guess is correct.).
{{ instruction_screen_12 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 13 of 17: Underestimate treatment payment rule: Explains that 150 cents go to charity if guess is too high, X cents go to self if guess is too low, and X cents go to self if guess is correct.).
{{ instruction_screen_13 }}

Type 'ok' to confirm you have read and understood these instructions.

Please carefully read the following experiment instructions (page 14 of 17: Overestimate treatment charity payment detail: If guess is too high, charity receives a donation of a specified amount.).
